# BLoC Layer Rules

## Bloc, never Cubit
- ‚ùå NEVER extend `Cubit` ‚Äî always use `Bloc<Event, State>`
- Every BLoC must have a typed sealed `Event` class and a `State` class

## Race conditions ‚Äî bloc_concurrency
Use `bloc_concurrency` transformers for all async event handlers:

```dart
import 'package:bloc_concurrency/bloc_concurrency.dart';

// ‚úÖ GOOD ‚Äî user_config ThemeBloc
ThemeBloc(...) : super(const ThemeState()) {
  on<ThemeStarted>(_onStarted, transformer: droppable());       // ignore taps while loading
  on<ThemeModeChanged>(_onModeChanged, transformer: sequential()); // queue saves
  on<ThemeSystemRefreshed>(_onSystemRefreshed, transformer: restartable()); // only latest
}

// ‚ùå BAD ‚Äî no transformer; concurrent taps can corrupt state
on<ThemeModeChanged>(_onModeChanged);
```

## Imports
- ‚ùå NO imports from any `data/` layer ‚Äî BLoC only sees domain (usecases, entities, failures)
- ‚ùå NO `Analytics.track(...)` calls ‚Äî analytics belong exclusively in UseCases
- ‚úÖ `flutter_bloc`, `bloc_concurrency`, `injectable`, `freezed_annotation`, own feature's `domain/`, `core/bloc/`

## State structure
Use `StateStatus` for async status and `Failure?` (typed field) for errors. Never use `String? errorMessage`.

```dart
// ‚ùå BAD ‚Äî current violation in user_config
@freezed
sealed class ThemeState with _$ThemeState {
  const factory ThemeState({
    @Default(StateStatus.initial) StateStatus status,
    String? errorMessage,    // ‚ùå raw string, loses type info
  }) = _ThemeState;
}

// ‚úÖ GOOD
@freezed
sealed class ThemeState with _$ThemeState {
  const factory ThemeState({
    AppThemeMode? themeMode,
    AppThemeMode? systemThemeMode,
    AppThemeMode? appliedThemeMode,
    @Default(StateStatus.initial) StateStatus status,
    Failure? failure,        // ‚úÖ typed Failure keeps FailureType for UI routing
  }) = _ThemeState;
}
```

For features with input fields, use `FieldState<T>` ‚Äî never `TextEditingController`:

```dart
// ‚úÖ GOOD ‚Äî hypothetical user_config profile edit state
@freezed
sealed class UserConfigEditState with _$UserConfigEditState {
  const factory UserConfigEditState({
    @Default(StateStatus.initial) StateStatus status,
    Failure? failure,
    @Default(FieldState(value: '')) FieldState<String> displayName,
    @Default(FieldState(value: '')) FieldState<String> email,
  }) = _UserConfigEditState;
}
```

## inlineError ‚Üí FieldState mapping
If `failure.type == FailureType.inlineError`, map to the specific `FieldState` ‚Äî never surface as top-level `failure`:

```dart
result.fold(
  (failure) {
    if (failure.type == FailureType.inlineError) {
      // Map to the specific field ‚Äî keep out of top-level failure
      emit(state.copyWith(
        displayName: state.displayName.copyWith(
          status: FieldStatus.invalid,
          error: failure.message,
        ),
      ));
    } else {
      emit(state.copyWith(status: StateStatus.error, failure: failure));
    }
  },
  (_) => emit(state.copyWith(status: StateStatus.success, failure: null)),
);
```

## File naming
Files must be prefixed with feature name:
- ‚úÖ `user_config_theme_bloc.dart`, `user_config_theme_event.dart`, `user_config_theme_state.dart`
- ‚ùå `theme_bloc.dart`, `bloc.dart`, `state.dart`
